With congressional negotiations regarding gun reform dominating the headlines in the wake of the Buffalo and Uvalde shootings, this week I decided to take a look at the issue of firearm mortality in the United States. The following graphics provide a brief insight into Americaâ€™s gun violence epidemic.

## Visualizing the School Shooting Crisis

The following map provides a visual representation of the 338 school shootings that have occurred since the Columbine High Shool shooting in 1999. Each circle represents a single incident, and the size of the circles indicate the number of casualties involved.[^1]
![school shootings map](images/school_shootings.jpg)

## Analyzing the Assocation between Gun Ownership and Firearm Mortality

The following scatter plot shows gun ownership in each state (expressed as a percentage of the population) versus firearm deaths per 100,000 people.
